communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All videos, emails, memorandums, reports, and investigations related to the escape of detainees from Delaney Hall on June 12, 2025.  
All complaints about Delaney Hall since May 1, 2025. 
All policies and directives regarding access to counsel at Delaney Hall.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Lara S Nochomovitz

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

- Any memos, emails, and/or policies drafted between January 20, 2020 and January 19, 2025, related to the effort between ATF, DEA, FBI, US Marshals, and HSI to locate and interview at-risk unaccompanied alien children who entered the United States over the past four years.

- Any memos, reports, and/or emails drafted between January 20, 2020 and January 19, 2025 quantifying the number and/or percentage of children identified as abused, trafficked, neglected, or exploited through Unaccompanied Alien Children Operations and/or other HSI wellness checks on at-risk unaccompanied alien children. 

- All trainings, memos, and/or policies used between January 20, 2020 and January 19, 2025 about communicating with children and/or using trauma-informed interviewing skills provided to agents completing wellness checks on at-risk unaccompanied alien children.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Lara S Nochomovitz

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Indiana Access to Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. Organization Audit in Flock.
The report should include data logged from the period of January 1st, to the date this request is processed. Per Flock's documentation, the Organization Audit is available within the Insights tab and is defined as searches done within the agency.

2. Network Audit in Flock.
The report should include data logged from the period of January 1st, to the date this request is processed. Per Flock's documentation, the Network Audit is available within the Insights tab and is defined as searches of the organization’s Flock network by any agency in the Flock System.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

garment
